panels.description: The percentage of CPU used by an instance.
panels.title: CPUUtilization

panels.description: The number of connections open on an instance taken at a one-minute frequency.
panels.title: Database Connections

panels.description: The amount of available random access memory, in bytes.
panels.title: Free Memory

panels.description: This metric reports the amount of storage available to each instance for temporary tables and logs. This value depends on the instance class. You can increase the amount of free storage space for an instance by choosing a larger instance class for your instance.
panels.title: Free Local Storage

panels.description: The amount of time, in seconds, that the instance has been running.
panels.title: Engine Uptime

panels.description: The amount of lag, in milliseconds, when replicating updates from the primary instance to a replica instance.
panels.title: DB Instance ReplicaLag

panels.description: The average amount of time taken per disk I/O operation.
panels.title: Read Latency

panels.description: The average amount of time, in milliseconds, taken per disk I/O operation.
panels.title: Write Latency

panels.description: The number of concurrent write requests to the distributed storage volume.
panels.title: Disk Queue Depth

panels.description: The number of queries issued in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Opcounters Query

panels.description: The number of insert operations issued in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Opcounters Insert

panels.description: The number of update operations issued in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Opcounters Update

panels.description: The number of delete operations issued in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Opcounters Delete

panels.description: The number of getmores issued in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Opcounters Getmore

panels.description: The number of commands issued in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Opcounters Command

panels.description: The number of returned documents in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Documents Returned

panels.description: The number of inserted documents in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Documents Inserted

panels.description: The number of updated documents in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Documents Updated

panels.description: The number of deleted documents in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Documents Deleted

panels.description: The number of transactions started on an instance in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Transactions Started

panels.description: The number of transactions committed on an instance in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Transactions Committed

panels.description: The number of transactions aborted on an instance in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Transactions Aborted

panels.description: The number of documents deleted by a TTLMonitor in a one-minute period.
panels.title: TTLDeletedDocuments

panels.description: The number of requests that are throttled due to low available memory in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Low Mem Num Operations Throttled

panels.description: The queue depth for requests that are throttled due to low available memory taken at a one-minute frequency.
panels.title: Low Mem Throttle Queue Depth

panels.description: The maximum queue depth for requests that are throttled due to low available memory in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Low Mem Throttle Max Queue Depth

panels.description: The percentage of index requests that are served by the buffer cache. You might see a spike greather than 100% for the metric right after you drop an index, collection or database. This will automatically be corrected after 60 seconds. This limitation will be fixed in a future patch update.
panels.title: Index Buffer Cache HitRatio

panels.description: The percentage of requests that are served by the buffer cache.
panels.title: Buffer Cache HitRatio

panels.description: The number of cursors open on an instance taken at a one-minute frequency.
panels.title: Database Cursors

panels.description: The maximum number of open cursors on an instance in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Database Cursors Max

panels.description: The number of cursors that timed out in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Database Cursors TimedOut

panels.description: The number of transactions open on an instance taken at a one-minute frequency.
panels.title: Transactions Open

panels.description: The maximum number of transactions open on an instance in a one-minute period.
panels.title: Transactions Open Max

panels.description: The average number of bytes read from disk per second.
panels.title: Read Throughput

panels.description: The average number of disk read I/O operations per second. Amazon DocumentDB reports read and write IOPS separately, and on one-minute intervals.
panels.title: Read IOPS

panels.description: The average number of bytes written to disk per second.
panels.title: Write Throughput

panels.description: The average number of disk write I/O operations per second. When used on a cluster level, WriteIOPs are evaluated across all instances in the cluster. Read and write IOPS are reported separately, on 1-minute intervals.
panels.title: Write IOPS

panels.description: The amount of network throughput, in bytes per second, received from clients by each instance in the cluster. This throughput doesn't include network traffic between instances in the cluster and the cluster volume.
panels.title: Network Receive Throughput

panels.description: The amount of network throughput, in bytes per second, sent to clients by each instance in the cluster. This throughput doesn't include network traffic between instances in the cluster and the cluster volume.
panels.title: Network Transmit Throughput

panels.description: The amount of network throughput, in bytes per second, both received from and transmitted to clients by each instance in the Amazon DocumentDB cluster. This throughput doesn't include network traffic between instances in the cluster and the cluster volume.
panels.title: Network Throughput
